----------------------------------------------------
Export managed Gold data to ADLS, then load Synapse
----------------------------------------------------
Databricks reads the managed Gold table using its table name, selects only the required daily records, and writes them into a separate ADLS folder as Parquet files. ADF then copies those Parquet files into a Synapse staging table. Finally, a Synapse stored procedure validates and moves the data into the final warehouse table.


Managed Gold Delta table
        ↓
Databricks reads table by name
        ↓
Filter current Batch ID / date
        ↓
Write filtered data to external ADLS export folder
        ↓
ADF Copy Activity
        ↓
Synapse staging table
        ↓
Validation
        ↓
Update existing records + insert new records
        ↓
Final Synapse table

In our Telekom broadband project, the Gold layer was maintained as Unity Catalog managed Delta tables in Databricks. Because it was a managed table, we accessed it using the catalog, schema, and table name, rather than depending on its internal ADLS path.
To load incremental data into Synapse Dedicated SQL Pool, ADF first called a Databricks notebook. The notebook read the Gold table, filtered only the current records using the Batch ID, business date, or modified timestamp, and wrote those records as Parquet files into a controlled, batch-specific ADLS export folder.
ADF then used a Copy Activity to move the Parquet files from the export folder into a Synapse staging table. After loading, we compared the Gold export count with the Synapse staging count and checked for null or duplicate business keys.
If validation passed, ADF called a Synapse stored procedure. For existing customer or product records, the procedure updated the final table. For new records, it inserted them. Finally, ADF updated the warehouse watermark and audit status to Completed.
We used the external export folder as a temporary interface between the managed Gold table and Synapse. This allowed us to process only the current incremental batch, validate the data, and restart the warehouse load without reading the complete Gold table again



